# Example RTTM (Rich Transcription Time Marked) Reference File
# Place this in annotations/reference.rttm
# Format: RTTM 1.2 specification
#
# Each line format:
# SPEAKER <filename> <channel> <start-time> <duration> <confidence> <speaker-id> <speech-type> <speech-mode>
#
# Example for ES2002a meeting:
# - Filename: ES2002a.Mix-Headset.wav (or just ES2002a)
# - Channel: 1 (main channel)
# - Start-time: seconds from start
# - Duration: duration in seconds
# - Confidence: always <NA>
# - Speaker-id: unique speaker identifier (e.g., SPK0001)
# - Speech-type: always <NA> for diarization
# - Speech-mode: always <NA> for diarization

SPEAKER ES2002a 1 0.000 5.230 <NA> SPK0001 <NA> <NA>
SPEAKER ES2002a 1 5.230 3.890 <NA> SPK0002 <NA> <NA>
SPEAKER ES2002a 1 9.120 4.450 <NA> SPK0001 <NA> <NA>
SPEAKER ES2002a 1 13.570 2.120 <NA> SPK0003 <NA> <NA>
SPEAKER ES2002a 1 15.690 3.850 <NA> SPK0002 <NA> <NA>
SPEAKER ES2002a 1 19.540 1.760 <NA> SPK0001 <NA> <NA>
SPEAKER ES2002a 1 21.300 2.240 <NA> SPK0003 <NA> <NA>
SPEAKER ES2002a 1 23.540 4.120 <NA> SPK0002 <NA> <NA>

# Tool: Generate RTTM with Audacity + PyAnnote export plugin
# Or manually time each speaker turn from reference transcript
#
# Import tools:
#   from pyannote.database.util import load_rttm
#   rttm = load_rttm("annotations/reference.rttm")
#
# When reference.rttm exists in annotations/ folder,
# the main.py script will automatically compute DER (Diarization Error Rate)
